achholz, at a phase angle of 30 degrees which showed a\ntypical red slope, rising from 2% at 650nm to 3% at 950nm in two different\nobservations (+1.0 and +0.9% per 1000 Angstroms).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Aug 2006 19:30:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
